Description: Two joining fragments of lip and wall with handle root of an East Greek pottery double eye-cup; interior glazed with added white decoration, 'tree' in lip zone, bands below; exterior: right half of panel of double cup; eyes framed by sets of six verticals and varied filling ornament; handle glazed; inscription on interior.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.388)
